- **Entity tokens** (anything hosted to a wall / floor / roof / level / room): each entity parametrised as `(host_id, t_along_host, Œ¥_offset_normal, scale, rotation)`. **Placements are host-referenced from the start, so geometry constraints are preserved by the representation.** A door cannot float because it is parametrically tied to a wall + along-wall position.

